# Styling Karibloom

## Variables CSS (src/styles/variables.css)

Adapter les couleurs au client :

```css
:root {
  --color-black: #000000;
  --color-black-soft: #0a0a0a;
  --color-white: #FFFFFF;

  /* Couleur principale (adapter au client) */
  --color-primary: #D4AF37;
  --color-primary-light: #F4E5C2;
  --color-primary-deep: #B38728;
  --color-primary-shine: #FCF6BA;
  --gradient-primary-metallic: linear-gradient(135deg, #BF953F, #FCF6BA, #B38728, #FBF5B7, #AA771C);

  --color-gray: #333333;
  --color-gray-medium: #666666;
  --color-gray-light: #B0B0B0;

  --font-heading: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
  --font-body: 'Inter', sans-serif;

  --transition: all 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
  --ease-luxe: cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);

  --glass-bg: rgba(10, 10, 10, 0.6);
  --glass-blur: blur(12px);
  --glass-border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);

  --border-radius: 12px;
  --radius-lg: 16px;
  --shadow-primary: 0 8px 24px rgba(212, 175, 55, 0.2);
}
```

## Effets

```css
/* Shimmer text */
.shimmer-primary {
  background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--color-primary-deep), var(--color-primary-shine), var(--color-primary-deep), var(--color-primary-shine), var(--color-primary-deep));
  background-size: 200% auto;
  -webkit-background-clip: text;
  -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
  animation: shimmer 5s linear infinite;
}
@keyframes shimmer { to { background-position: 200% center; } }

/* Glassmorphism */
.glass-card {
  background: var(--glass-bg);
  backdrop-filter: var(--glass-blur);
  border: var(--glass-border);
  border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
}

/* Fade-in au scroll */
[data-animate="fade"] {
  opacity: 0;
  transform: translateY(30px);
  transition: opacity 0.6s var(--ease-luxe) var(--fade-delay, 0.18s),
              transform 0.6s var(--ease-luxe) var(--fade-delay, 0.18s);
}
[data-animate="fade"].is-visible {
  opacity: 1;
  transform: translateY(0);
}
```

## Tailwind Config

Utiliser HSL CSS variables pour les couleurs via shadcn/ui pattern. Dark mode `["class"]`. Plugin `tailwindcss-animate`.

